summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling its previous resolutions on the International Tribunal for the former Yugoslavia, particularly resolutions 1503 (2003) and 1534 (2004) which called on the Tribunal to complete its work by 2010,

Noting the Tribunal's assessment that it will not complete its work by 2010,

Urging the Tribunal to expedite its work,

Noting concerns about staff retention,

Acting under Chapter VII of the UN Charter,

1. Authorizes Judge Kevin Parker to complete the Đorđević case beyond his term expiry on 31 December 2010, with the case to be completed by February 2011;
2. Authorizes Judge Uldis Kinis to complete the Gotovina et al. case beyond his term expiry on 31 December 2010, with the case to be completed by March 2011;
3. Allows Judge Kinis to serve beyond the cumulative period provided under the Tribunal's Statute;
4. Reiterates the importance of adequate staffing for the Tribunal to complete its work expeditiously, and calls on the Secretariat and relevant UN bodies to assist the Registrar in finding solutions;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
